No. R-108. House concurrent resolution congratulating the 2025 Thetford Academy
inductees into the National Technical Honor Society.
(H.C.R.88)
Offered by Representatives Masland of Thetford and Holcombe of Norwich
Whereas, juniors and seniors who are enrolled at Thetford Academy and desire to
pursue a technical education curriculum are eligible to attend the River Bend Career and
Technical Center in Bradford, and
Whereas, River Bend Career and Technical Center offers a broad set of curriculum
choices in the realm of technical education from which students may select to focus, and
Whereas, students who excel in their studies at River Bend Career and Technical
Center, regardless of their subject specialization, may be selected for membership in the
National Technical Honor Society, and
Whereas, receipt of this special recognition is offered to students “who demonstrate
scholastic excellence, honesty, dependability, and responsibility, as well as leadership,
good citizenship, and pride in their work,” and
Whereas, on March 12, 2025, six jointly enrolled students became proud members of
the National Technical Honor Society, and
Whereas, these students and their subject specializations are Hunter Clay
(construction), Heidi Hewes (health science), Joshua King (heavy equipment), Ashlyn
Osgood (emergency services), Rebecca Osgood (emergency services), and Dillon Vance
(construction), and each has demonstrated scholastic excellence meriting special
commendation, now therefore be it
Resolved by the Senate and House of Representatives:
That the General Assembly congratulates the 2025 Thetford Academy inductees into
the National Technical Honor Society, and be it further
Resolved: That the Secretary of State be directed to send a copy of this resolution to
each of the students recognized in this resolution.
